title: For Sale:  British Enfield Jungle Carbine
postcontent: An upcoming move has forced me to thin out my collection a bit.  The rifle you are viewing is a British Enfield Jungle Carbine.  These rifles were created in response to the British Army's request for a shortened version of the No. III and No. IV Enfield rifles which were accurate, but long and cumbersome.  The rifle you see was the result.  The jungle carbine was handy, manueverable and still packed the punch of the .303 British round.  Some say that these rifles suffered from less than adequate accuracy when compared to the long Enfields, and at ranges over 500 yards that may be true, but in my experience this rifle has been very accurate up to 250 yards when shooting at 18 inch targets.  The rifle is in very nice condition, shoots well, includes one detachable 10 rd. magazine and a leather sling.  It has ben properly cared for by a former US Navy marksman.  Cash sale only, no trades.  Thank you for viewing!
